              <div class="control-group">
                <div class="control-label">Time axis</div>
                <div class="control-row-tight">
                  <button onclick="panTime(-1)" class="mini-tool" aria-label="Pan earlier">‹</button>
                  <button onclick="zoomTime(1)" class="mini-tool" aria-label="Zoom in">+</button>
                  <button onclick="zoomTime(-1)" class="mini-tool" aria-label="Zoom out">−</button>
                  <button onclick="panTime(1)" class="mini-tool" aria-label="Pan later">›</button>
                  <button onclick="resetTimeAxis()" class="mini-tool" aria-label="Reset time axis">↺</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div id="timeWindowReadout" class="control-note"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Time series chart -->
          <div class="section-card" style="padding:1rem">
            <div class="chart-header">
              <span class="chart-title">Time series</span>
              <span class="chart-meta">Aligned observations</span>
            </div>
            <div id="timeSeriesChart" class="chart-container"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Scatter chart -->
          <div class="section-card" style="padding:1rem">
            <div class="chart-header">
              <span class="chart-title">Scatter: radiation vs temperature</span>
              <span class="chart-meta" id="resolutionBadge">Monthly pairs</span>
            </div>
            <div id="scatterChart" class="chart-container"></div>
            <div id="scatterNote" class="chart-footnote"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Correlation analysis -->
          <div class="section-card">
            <div class="section-heading">Correlation analysis</div>
            <div class="metric-grid">
              <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">Pearson r</div>
                <div id="pearsonR" class="metric-value accent">—</div>
              </div>
              <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">r² (explained variance)</div>
                <div id="rSquared" class="metric-value">—</div>
              </div>
              <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">p-value (approx)</div>
                <div id="pValue" class="metric-value success">—</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="contribution-box">
              <div class="contribution-label">Contribution score</div>
              <div id="contributionScore" class="contribution-value">—</div>
              <div class="contribution-note">Sunshine explains a portion of temperature variance. Clouds, circulation, albedo, land/sea effects, and station exposure also play major roles.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div><!-- /#labContent -->

        <!-- Data sources & methodology — always at the foot -->
        <details class="expander sources-expander">
          <summary>Data sources &amp; methodology</summary>
          <div class="expander-body">
            <dl class="sources-list">
              <dt>Temperature — GHCN-Monthly v4</dt>
              <dd>Global Historical Climatology Network Monthly (GHCNm v4) dataset, served via klymot.com. Raw and Adjusted (homogenised) records. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1175/JCLI-D-18-0094.1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Menne et al., 2018</a>.</dd>
              <dt>Homogenisation</dt>
              <dd>Adjusted records use pairwise homogeneity methods for non-climatic shifts. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1175/2008JCLI2263.1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Menne &amp; Williams, 2009</a>.</dd>
              <dt>Shortwave radiation</dt>
              <dd>Monthly totals of global horizontal irradiance (MJ/m²) — total downwelling shortwave radiation at the surface, the quantity measured by a pyranometer.</dd>
              <dt>Station network history</dt>
              <dd>Cumulative station counts derived from the <a href="https://github.com/AssessingSolar/solarstations" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AssessingSolar/solarstations</a> catalog on GitHub. Milestone events curated by hand.</dd>
            </dl>
            <p class="sources-footer">This is a neutral exploration tool. Correlation does not imply causation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
